      • setClientBlockUnmappedActions

        public SecurityConfig setClientBlockUnmappedActions(boolean clientBlockUnmappedActions)
        Description copied from class: SecurityConfig
        Block or allow actions, submitted as tasks in an Executor from clients and have no permission mappings.

        Executors:

        • IExecutorService
        • IScheduledExecutorService
        • DurableExecutorService
        Overrides:
        setClientBlockUnmappedActions in class SecurityConfig
        Parameters:
        clientBlockUnmappedActions -
      • True: Blocks all actions that have no permission mapping
      • False: Allows all actions that have no permission mapping

      • getClientPermissionConfigs

        public Set<PermissionConfig> getClientPermissionConfigs()
        Returns existing client permissions as an unmodifiable Set. You may use this set to create your client permissions set and pass it setClientPermissionConfigs(Set) to update client permissions.
